The Ministry of Foreign Affairs has advertised job vacancies on behalf of two entities based in Morocco and Kazakhstan. Both the Islamic Centre for Development of Trade, Morocco; and the Islamic Organization for Food Security, Kazakhstan, had advertised the vacancies on their respective websites, and Nigeria’s foreign affairs ministry had drawn Nigerians’ attention to them. The ministry used its Twitter handle @NigeriaMFA to do the advertorial. Most of the few persons who responded to the tweet were, however, concerned that they might not qualify since they were neither Muslim nor Arabic speakers. See the tweet: 